Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Bioactive Glass Market

Bioactive glass market will expect to grow at a rate of 14.0% for the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Bioactive glass market report analyses the growth, which is currently being growing due to the increasing number of population across the globe.

Bioactive glass is a type of bioactive material that, particularly in dentistry, has a number of applications in the medical industry. Bioactive glass is used as scaffolds, bone grafts and also as a coating material in the case of dental implants. The bioactive glass consists primarily of calcium, sodium, phosphorus and silicon. Bioactive glass is significantly used in tissue engineering applications owing to characteristics such as superior osteoconductivity, biocompatibility, bioactivity and biodegradability.

The growing usages of the product in tissue engineering applications owing to characteristics such as superior osteoconductivity, biocompatibility, bioactivity and biodegradability, rapid urbanization across the globe, rising levels of per capita expenditure on healthcare, rising number of clinical applications of the product, rising levels of disposable income of the people, increasing incidence of musculoskeletal ailments and chronic skeletal conditions, emergence of nanotechnology in tissue engineering along with rising shift from bioinert to bioactive materials are some of the major as well as important factors which will likely to accelerate the growth of the bioactive glass market in the projected timeframe of 2021-2028. On the other hand, rising need of high-quality medical services along with growing trends of merger and acquisitions which will further contribute by generating massive opportunities that will lead to the growth of the bioactive glass market in the above mentioned projected timeframe.

Increasing need of high capital investment in terms of technology along with high cost of medical facilities which will likely to act as market restraints factor for the growth of the bioactive glass in the above mentioned projected timeframe. Stringent regulations, and low requirement in developing countries which will become the biggest and foremost challenge for the growth of the market.

